{"name": "flowable-rpaframework-client", "metadata": {"name": "flowable.rpaframework-client", "version": "1.0.1", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": "Apache License, Version 2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["flowable.external-worker-client"], "summary": "Flowable client to be used with rpaframework. This client connects to a Flowable instance via external worker and executes rpaframework robots or robocorp tasks or actions.", "upload_time": 1732787361}, "documentation": ["# Flowable RPA Framework Client\n\n[License:\n![license](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/l/plug.svg)](https://github.com/flowable/flowable-external-client-python/blob/main/LICENSE)\n\n![Flowable Actions CI](https://github.com/flowable/flowable-external-client-python/actions/workflows/main.yml/badge.svg?branch=main)\n\nThis is a python module to connect a Flowable installation through an external worker with a RPA framework task.\nThis allows to execute an RPA framework task from a business process with BPMN or a case diagram CMMN.\nThe application is started with a task definition from RPA framework and connects to an external worker topic.\nWhen using the RPA framework task in Flowable, it is possible to specify a task name.\nIn the task, the specific task specified will be executed and the result will be sent back to the process.\nIt is required that the variables in the diagram match exactly the variables inside the RPA framework task.\n\n## Installation\n\nTo install the Flowable RPA framework client, execute the following command:\n\n```\npip install flowable.rpaframework-client\n```\n\n## Sample\n\nThe following [diagram BPMN](docs/rpaframeworkExample.bpmn) illustrates a basic usage of the RPA framework task:\n\n![Simple BPMN diagram with a start event, a RPA Framework task and an end event](docs/rpaframeworkExample.png)\n\nThe following example `myTask.robot` can be used as an RPA framework task:\n```\n*** Settings ***\nLibrary\t\tflowable.rpaframework_client.API\n\n*** Tasks ***\nGet weather forecast\n    ${city}=\t\tflw input\tcity\n    ${days}=\t\tflw input\tdays\n    ${length}=      Get Length  ${city}\n    ${temperature}=     Evaluate    ${days} * ${length}\n    flw output\t\ttemperature     ${temperature}\n```\n\nThe RPA Framework worker can be started with the following command:\n```sh\npython -m flowable.rpaframework_client --flowable-token <your-token> myTopic myTask.robot\n```\n\nYou can request `<your-token>` at the [Flowable Trial](https://trial.flowable.com/work/) by clicking at the bottom left on your user and go to Settings.\nOnce in the settings, choose \"Access Token\" and press the button \"New token\".\nAfter providing name and the validity, the token is generated and can be set.\n\nOnce the module is started and a process instance is created, it will automatically execute the RPA framework action and returns the result to Flowable.\nThe Python module will keep running until stopped to process potential additional jobs.\n\n## Authentication\n\nNext to the cloud authentication, it's possible to authenticate against other hosts.\nThe hostname can be specified with `--flowable-host`.\n\nFor the authentication there are two possibilities:\n\n1. Providing a bearer token with the `--flowable-token <token>` attribute.\n2. Providing basic authentication with `--flowable-username <username>` and `--flowable-password <password>`\n"], "modules": [{"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.API", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.API.API", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.API.API.flw_input", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.API.API.flw_output", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": {"name": "any", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.API.API.result", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.call_python_module", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.call_python_module.call_python_module", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mod_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "env", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.__main__", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.__main__.parser", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.__main__.args", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.__main__.topic", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.__main__.auth", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.__main__.auth", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.__main__.auth", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.__main__.client", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flowable.rpaframework_client.__main__.job_handler", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name"